611. This work was also supported by World Bank grants ACE-019 and ACE-IMPACT; The Rockefeller Foundation (grant 2021 HTH); The Africa CDC through the African Society of Laboratory Medicine (ASLM) (grant INV018978), and the Science for Africa Foundation. I.F.O. is supported by the Wellcome Trust Hosts, Pathogens &amp; Global Health programme (Wellcome Trust, grant 218471/Z/19/Z) in partnership with Tackling Infectious Disease to Benefit Africa. P.L. is supported by the European Union’s Horizon 2020 project MOOD (grant 874850) and by the Research Foundation—Flanders (Fonds voor Wetenschappelijk Onderzoek—Vlaanderen; G0D5117N, G005323N and G051322N). A.R., A. O’Toole, P.L. and M.A.S. are supported by the Wellcome Trust Collaborators Award 206298/Z/17/Z (ARTIC network). We thank the Africa CDC for mpox diagnostic reagents provided to the surveillance system in Cameroon and Advanced Micro Devices for the donation of massively parallel computing hardware.</p></div></div></section><section aria-labelledby="author-information" data-title="Author information"><div class="c-article-section" id="author-information-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="author-information">Author information</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="author-information-content"><span class="c-article-author-information__subtitle u-visually-hidden" id="author-notes">Author notes</span><ol class="c-article-author-information__list"><li class="c-article-author-information__item" id="na1"><p>These authors contributed equally: Edyth Parker, Ifeanyi F. Omah, Delia Doreen Djuicy</p></li><li class="c-article-author-information__item" id="na2"><p>These authors jointly supervised this work: Richard Njouom, Christian T. Happi</p></li></ol><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="affiliations">Authors and Affiliations</h3><ol class="c-article-author-affiliation__list"><li id="Aff1"><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__address">African 